# Verified Uses

## 2026-07-04 — ProjectHephaestus PR #1833 (issue #1811)

**Context**: Pipeline foundation layer implementation. Routing table mapped terminal failure reasons (no_pr, routes to FINISHED) to budget keys (ci_fix), causing incorrect budget deduction and test failures.

**Verification**:
- Test: `tests/unit/automation/pipeline/test_routing_properties.py`
- Property-based tests: 58 tests, all pass with hypothesis
- Terminal path fix: `"no_pr": None` (no budget consumed)
- Retry path fix: `"ci_fix": "ci_fix_budget"` (1 budget per item)
- CI: verified-ci (all checks passed)

**Commits**: Fixed in sub-agent code review response; tested in PR #1833.

## Lesson Applicability

- Used by: Pipeline automation, queue-based work-item routing
- Applies to: Any system with terminal vs retry path routing tables
- Scope: Test fixtures, property-based testing, routing contracts
